-- Galleon Case Yields Suit Against Ex-Fund Adviser Hardin for Insider Trades
-- B y   G r e g   C h a n g
-- 2010-11-12T22:45:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-12/galleon-case-yields-suit-against-ex-fund-adviser-hardin-for-insider-trades.html
Thomas Hardin, a former managing
director at hedge fund investment adviser Lanexa Management LLC,
was sued by the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission for
insider trading of the securities of Hilton, Google and Kronos.
The suit is in connection with the Galleon Management probe, the
SEC said in a statement on its website.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
